So, we need to show `‚ąĎ i : ‚Ąē, |(1 / i)|^2025 < ‚ąě`.
Since `i : ‚Ąē`, `i ‚Č• 0`.
For `i = 0`, `(1 / 0)` is `0` in Lean's real numbers. So `|(1/0)|^2025 = 0^2025 = 0`.
For `i ‚Č• 1`, `|(1 / i)| = 1 / i`. So we need `‚ąĎ i : ‚Ąē, (1 / i)^2025 < ‚ąě`.
This is a p-series `‚ąĎ 1/i^p` with `p = 2025`.
Since `p > 1` (as `2025 > 1`), the p-series converges. Therefore, the sum is finite, which means `GEO` is in `‚Ąď^2025`.

